                    <p>Many loanwords (e.g., ballpoint pen, gas, truck) are derived from Japanese. While usage among the youth is declining, the government is actively promoting a "Mother Tongue Revival" to preserve this cultural legacy rooted in traditional markets and daily life.</p>
