                <div class="culture-text">
                    <h3>4. The Monsoons Define the Seasons</h3>
                    <p>In Taiwan, what determines your outfit is the "wind direction."</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>North (Winter):</strong> Influenced by the <strong>Northeast Monsoon</strong>, Taipei's winter is often rainy. The high humidity creates a "bone-chilling" cold, so carrying rain gear is essential.</li>
                        <li><strong>South (Summer):</strong> Influenced by the <strong>Southwest Monsoon</strong>, the south often has afternoon thunderstorms in summer. While hot and humid, it brings abundant water resources.</li>
                    </ul>
